This walkthrough documents the implementation and verification of the Security Layer for the AlgoPath application. We successfully created stateless password hashing and JWT utility services under `backend/app/services/` and wrote a complete unit test suite validating their functionality and error handling.

---

## Changes Implemented

### 1. Dependencies

* **[requirements.txt](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/requirements.txt)**: Added `bcrypt>=4.0.0` explicitly as a production dependency to avoid passlib version conflicts.
* **[requirements-dev.txt](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/requirements-dev.txt)**: Created new file and added `pytest>=8.0.0` as a development/test tool dependency.

### 2. Core Security Services

* **[password_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/password_service.py)**:
  * Implemented a stateless helper class `PasswordService`.
  * Added `hash_password(password: str) -> str` using `bcrypt` (independent of database or framework).
  * Added `verify_password(password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool` with robust exception protection for invalid hash formats.
* **[jwt_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/jwt_service.py)**:
  * Implemented class `JWTService` reading configuration from settings.
  * Added custom exception handlers: `JWTServiceError`, `TokenExpiredError`, `TokenInvalidError`.
  * Added `create_access_token(subject: str) -> str` which formats payloads strictly with `sub` and `exp` claims. Uses timezone-aware UTC datetime computation.
  * Added `verify_access_token(token: str) -> dict` doing signature/expiration checks and mapping exceptions to `TokenExpiredError` / `TokenInvalidError`.
  * Added `decode_access_token(token: str) -> dict` allowing decryption of expired tokens (skipping expiration checks) to read claims while maintaining signature validation.

### 3. Unit Test Suite

* **[test_password_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/tests/test_password_service.py)**:
  * Unit tests validating:
    * Password hashing format (starts with `$2`).
    * Correct verification.
    * Mismatched password rejection.
    * Graceful rejection of empty/malformed hashes.
* **[test_jwt_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/tests/test_jwt_service.py)**:
  * Unit tests validating:
    * Token structure containing only the `sub` and `exp` claims.
    * Successful verification of valid tokens.
    * Expired tokens raise `TokenExpiredError`.
    * Tampered signature tokens raise `TokenInvalidError`.
    * Malformed strings raise `TokenInvalidError`.
    * Verification bypass for expired tokens under `decode_access_token`.

